videoSnippet.title: A Super Fun Game! || Dominguez vs Aronian || FIDE Chess.com Nations Cup (2020)
videoSnippet.description:
Follow me on Instagram for extra content and notifications https://www.instagram.com/agadmator/

Leinier Perez Dominguez vs Levon Aronian
FIDE Chess.com Online Nations Cup (2020), 6.5.2020
Petrov, classical attack, Marshall variation (C42)

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Nxe5 d6 4. Nf3 Nxe4 5. d4 d5 6. Bd3 Bd6 7. O-O O-O 8. c4 c6 9. Qc2 h6 10. Re1 Be6 11. cxd5 cxd5 12. Bxe4 dxe4 13. Qxe4 Bd5 14. Qg4 Qd7 15. Qxd7 Nxd7 16. Nc3 Bxf3 17. gxf3 Bb4 18. Bd2 Rfd8 19. Ne4 Bxd2 20. Nxd2 Nf6 21. Nb3 b6 22. Rac1 Nd5 23. a3 Rd6 24. Re4 Rad8 25. Kf1 a5 26. a4 g5 27. Rc4 Kg7 28. Re1 Kg6 29. Nd2 Nb4 30. Nb3 Nd3 31. Re2 Nf4 32. Re1 Rf6 33. Nd2 Nd3 34. Rb1 Rf4 35. Rc6+ Kg7 36. Rxb6 Rdxd4 37. b3 Nxf2 38. Ke2 Rh4 39. Nf1 Nd3 40. Rb5 Nf4+ 41. Kf2 Rd3 42. Re5 Rc3 43. Rxa5 Rh3 44. Rb5 Rhxf3+ 45. Kg1 Rc2 46. Rb6 Rff2 47. a5 Rg2+ 48. Kh1 Nh3

The FIDE Chess.com Online Nations Cup is a 6-team double round-robin tournament taking place from 5-10 May 2020. Teams consist of 6 players, with 4 playing in each round. At least one woman must play in each match.

Players receive 25 minutes for the entire game, plus a 10-second increment starting from move one. No draw offers are allowed before move 30. The top 2 after the round-robin will play a Superfinal. Official website: chess.com
